cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper discusses normalization mechanisms for citation-based indicators of research performance, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the management and analysis of digital information, including citation data. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible categories as they involve the analysis and organization of large datasets. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible categories as they may involve the analysis of citation networks and the evaluation of research performance.
